10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Help Scout is best suited for small businesses, SaaS startups, customer focused teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Kommunicate, meanwhile, shines for mid size support teams, SaaS companies, hybrid bot+human support, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2011, Help Scout describes itself as \"Simple and human customer support platform with AI-powered features.\" Kommunicate, established in 2017, positions itself as \"AI chatbot platform with seamless human handoff for customer support.\" With 6 years between them, Help Scout brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Kommunicate offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Help Scout** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 6.0), more features (9 vs 8), more competitive pricing. However, this does not mean Kommunicate is a poor choice — far from it. Kommunicate excels in its own right, particularly for mid size support teams and SaaS companies.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value clean and simple shared inbox, go with Help Scout. If smooth bot-to-human handoff matters more to you, Kommunicate is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
